jobs_results.description:
A very exciting opportunity for a Project Manager who has experience in managing Data Analytics project, to join the Group Audit team in one of the leading Banks.

Mandatory Skill(s)
• Bachelor Degree in Computer Science or Information Systems disciplines;
• At least 6 years’ experience in project Delivery;
• Minimum 4 years of Project Management skills;
• Excellent ability of implementing Data Analytics project;
• Good exposure in banking Industry;
• Ability to work independently, manage stress and multitask in a fast paced environment;
• Excellent stakeholder management skills;
• Strong communication, presentation, documentation and negotiation skills.

Desirable Skill(s)
• Prior experience in consulting;
• PMP certification.

Responsibilities
• Responsible for the end to end timely and on budget delivery of Data Analytics Projects;
• Ensure the technical feasibility of the project by liaising with stakeholders in defining the scope, objectives and measure of success;
• Work closely... with the Business Users / Product Owners and communicate schedule of the progress and if required escalate to the management;;
• Responsible for creating a workplan/schedule for the activities required to successfully complete the project;
• Trace the financials on monthly basis;
• Plan and manage the risks and issues to avoid cost and schedule impact;
• Examine the quality of work done on regular basis ensuring that project standards are met
